ENSF400-Final-Project 1.0.0 API

This is the Demo application by Coveros. You can find plenty of documentation in the docs/ directory. It is listed on Github

When looking into each class, the following patterns may aid in your understanding.

  • Files that end with "Servlet" are the code that makes the application available to the outside world, that is, it is the definition of web API
  • Files that end with "Utils" are the business logic for a particular domain
Packages
Package
Description
com.coveros.training.authentication
Authentication mechanisms - usernames, passwords, etc.
com.coveros.training.authentication.domainobjects
Domain objects related to authentication
com.coveros.training.cartesianproduct
Calculates the cartesian product of multiple sets.
com.coveros.training.expenses
Calculates restaurant expenses that include alcohol, per government accounting rules.
com.coveros.training.helpers
Various helper classes that are used throughout the application.
com.coveros.training.library
Books and borrowers and that sort of thing.
com.coveros.training.library.domainobjects
These represent concepts within the library domain, like books, borrowers, loans.
com.coveros.training.mathematics
Interesting mathematics - adding things, Fibonacci sequence, Ackermann's formula, etc.
com.coveros.training.persistence
Classes that provide communication with the database
